description:
&lt;p&gt;Due to the internal promotion of the current post holder we have an excellent opportunity to become a band 7 Physiotherapist in Acute Older peoples Medicine&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post will be based across site at the RVI and or Freeman Hospitals as the service requires.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will provide a high standard of physiotherapy care to a highly complex patient group on Acute Older People’s Medicine, delivering in house training and service development for the speciality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;They will be an active member of the appropriate multi disciplinary team within the speciality area leading on Quality improvement and best practice models.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;They will be responsible for their own continued professional development and support staff in clinical supervision and appraisal.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Following a period of in-house assessment, induction and training (as appropriate), they will be expected to be part of the emergency duty on-call and weekend rota 1.4 weekend cover&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full time 37 hours 30 minutes/week&lt;/p&gt;
